4. Be7{ With our kingside setup complete, it's time to challenge the center with a pawn... but which one? }( { In fact, all three options are reasonable: }5.d4 { would transpose to Queen's pawn openings;  e4  (first prepared with }5.d3 { ) would be the King's Indian Attack (another good option) but our main approach in this course will be }5.c4 { . }{    }{ Why? Well, the  c4 -pawn lever plays very well with our bishop on  g2 , prying open the long diagonal. In many lines, we apply long-term pressure on the queenside after opening the long diagonal. } )( { And as always, I'm keeping an eye on the stats: }5.c4 { scores extremely well in practice! } )
