7. Bd7{ The only good move, but not an obvious one if you don't know it. Black correctly prioritizes development. }
8. Nxc4{ This simple recapture is rarely played, but I don't know why. It scores well in practice. The idea (apart from just taking a pawn) is to set up an annoying knight check on  d6  before Black can castle. }( 8.Na3 { is more popular, leading to very complex lines requiring a lot of memorization. } )
8. cxd4
9. Bf4{ It is important to do this immediately, setting up  Nd6  before Black has a chance to castle. }
9. Nd5
10. Nd6+
10. Bxd6
11. Bxd6
11. Nde7
12. Nd2
12. O-O
13. Qb3{ In exchange for the pawn, White has a powerful bishop pair and more active pieces. It's much easier to play for White. }
