8. Bxf3{ This is the most accurate. Black exchanges the bishop before we have a chance to play  Nd2  and recapture with the knight. }( 8...Nbd7 9.Nbd2 { is exactly such a scenario. } )
9. Bxf3
9. e6
10. Nd2{ Black's position is certainly very solid, but White has the bishop pair and a flexible pawn structure. We can connect the rooks with  Qc2  and perhaps start creeping forward with the center pawns. }
