9. d3{ White can finish development with  Bd2  and  O-O  (yep, it’s still legal!). It’s a complex position with all the pieces on the board, but Black’s weak dark squares on the kingside aren’t going away. Look for chances to trade off Black’s dark-squared bishop (e.g., with  Bg5  or  Ne4 ) at the right moment to accentuate the weak dark squares even more. }
