2. e4{ We're threatening to take over the center with  d4 , so Black's options are fairly limited. If they want to contest the center they have to play ... c5 , transposing to an Accelerated Dragon Sicilian. Or they can play ... Bg7 , allowing us to build a pawn center and go into the Modern Defense. }
2. Bg7
3. d4
3. d6
4. Bc4{ Continuing to develop the kingside and targeting Black's weak point on  f7 . }
4. Nf6
5. Qe2{ Getting the queen off the d-file to avoid a queen trade. Our plan is to castle and play  e5 . We don't want to play  Nc3  here because we may want to put a pawn on  c3  to support the center. }
5. O-O
6. O-O
6. Nc6
7. e5
7. dxe5( 7...Ne8 { would be a better try, but this is clearly very sad for Black. } )
8. dxe5
8. Ng4
9. Rd1{ The queen doesn't have a good square. }
9. Bd7
10. e6{ White is winning. }
